-- bot_no_seat_slow_v2.lua
-- 끝말잇기 hint bot — clean rewrite. OBSERVE-ONLY: never types, submits, or fires
-- any remote. It only READS GameData and shows a word for the human to type.
--
-- The ENGINE (between the markers below) is the racebot strategy + kt shell,
-- injected by build_bots.py from racebot.lua + kt_engine.lua (2026-07-06). The
-- strategy is the residual-relabel race engine (kkutu_research, measured 433:5
-- vs the old policy).
--
-- Why the class model: this build's GameData exposes only CurrentTurnPlayer /
-- StartingLetter / Players(+Lives) — NO word field. The opponent's exact word is
-- unobservable. But every played word shows up as a StartingLetter transition
-- (my-end -> new-letter). We record that transition's (start,end) CLASS and treat
-- all same-class words as interchangeable — the offline engine runs on the SAME
-- abstraction, which is why the port is exact.
--
-- Data: a SINGLE payload racebot_data.json (racebot-v2-refined: meta/syl2node/
-- avail[multi-source]/class_to/class_count/self_loop/static_loss/pools; directed
-- dueum baked into syl2node) replaces the old dict/routes/openers/racedata stack.
-- Consumption is driven by OBSERVED
-- transitions (state.play -> RaceBot:consumePair); the strategy only picks.

--
-- ⚙️ STRATEGY ENGINE below is SHARED with bot_chair.lua and INJECTED by
-- build_bots.py from racebot.lua + kt_engine.lua. Do NOT edit between the
-- markers here — edit those and re-run build_bots.py. Only the POSTLUDE after
-- ===ENGINE_END=== (onMyTurn=display, GUI, boot) is slow-specific.
-- ===ENGINE_BEGIN===
-- ---- racebot.lua (verbatim strategy module; wrapped so its locals stay nested) ----
RaceBot = (function()
--[[ racebot.lua — consumption-aware word-chain bot on THREE inputs only:
  ① my-turn signal + the syllable I must start with (nil = I open the round)
  ② server verdict on my own submissions (accepted / rejected)
  ③ round boundaries (roundStart) — required, see below

REFINED (directed 두음) engine. Payload = racebot-v2-refined (export_racebot.py):
a POSITION is an allowed-set (frozenset of permitted start syllables); a class
c has a MULTI-source avail[c] (positions it can be played from) and a SINGLE
class_to[c] (landing). This fixes the canonical bug where 이≡리≡니 merged into one
node and the bot offered live-REJECTED phantom words (a 리-start word when
required=이). Now outC[position] lists ONLY classes playable from that exact
allowed-set, so a proposal's first syllable is always ∈ allowed(required).

The bot never observes the opponent's words. It doesn't need to: a word is
strategically identical to every other word of the same refined class (the exact
abstraction the offline race engine is built on), and the opponent's word's class
is determined by (my last word's landing position -> the syllable I'm now
required to start with). So we track per-class remaining counts, decrement one on
every observed transition, and run the residual retrograde relabel + tier policy
on those counts — the algorithm that measured 748:0 offline (racesolver.py).

Multi-source specifics (mirror residual.py / race.py; the canonical port assumed
one source per class and was WRONG under 두음 splits):
- outC[p] = every class with p ∈ avail (fan over avail, not a single class_from).
- total[p] mirrors state.live: it counts by the PRIMARY source avail[c][1] only
  (word_first), so it stays byte-identical to the Python engine's conservative
  per-position count. Every PROVEN verdict uses the exact per-class `live`, never
  `total` (total is the heuristic opp count + the 한방 guard).
- relabel's WIN/LOSS wave fans a landing class back to EVERY source in avail.
- self-loop test is data.self_loop[c] (class_to ∈ avail), not class_from==to.

Known information gaps (deliberate, documented approximations):
- When the OPPONENT opens a round we see only the landing position, not the
  opener's start; we phantom-consume the largest live class landing there
  (error <= 1 word per opponent-opened round).
- A rejection is ambiguous (not-in-live-dict vs opponent-already-used-it).
  Per design: no analysis, just try the next word of the pool — words of one
  class are interchangeable, so the strategy choice needs no recompute.
- Opponent (non-opener) transition (myLanding -> required) may match several
  refined classes (distinct acceptor profiles sharing a source position + a
  landing). We consume the max-live match — sum-exact regardless of which,
  since only the count of consumed words affects the live total. On dueum=False
  toys avail is a singleton, so this is the canonical (from,to) lookup exactly.

Why roundStart is required (not inferable): without it, the first required
syllable of a new round would be mis-read as a chain transition from my LAST
word of the PREVIOUS round, corrupting a class count. Used words persist across
rounds (live match rule), so state must NOT reset between rounds — only the
chain anchor does.

Usage:
  local RaceBot = require(path.to.racebot)
  local bot = RaceBot.new(data)        -- data: decoded racebot_data payload
  bot:reset()                          -- new MATCH
  bot:roundStart(iOpen)                -- every round, incl. round 1
  local w = bot:myTurn(requiredSyl)    -- requiredSyl=nil means I open
  -- submit w; then EXACTLY ONE of:
  bot:accepted()                       -- server took it
  local w2 = bot:rejected()            -- refused; w2 = next try (nil = give up)
]]

local RaceBot = {}
RaceBot.__index = RaceBot

local UNKNOWN, WIN, LOSS = 0, 1, 2
local INF = 1e9
local OPEN_TOPK = 12        -- mirror racesolver._OPEN_TOPK
local OPEN_WORDS_PER_NODE = 2  -- opener rejections can mean the NODE is rule-
                               -- banned (필승 re-check), not the word: 2 tries
                               -- disambiguate dict-miss cheaply, then move on

-- Dictionary words are pure Hangul; every syllable is exactly 3 UTF-8 bytes.
local function firstSyl(w) return string.sub(w, 1, 3) end
local function lastSyl(w) return string.sub(w, -3) end

function RaceBot.new(data, opts)
    local self = setmetatable({}, RaceBot)
    self.data = data
    self.openProven = not (opts and opts.openProven == false)
    -- Exact (CBRS) layer. ON by default — it is the measured 40%->83.5%-vs-expert
    -- lever (the pre-CBRS chain policy loses to the corridor exploit). exactBudget
    -- is the CBRS visit cap per region-solve; live turn timer (~10s) easily fits
    -- it (largest region ~3ms in Python; Luau ~<0.1s). opts.exact==false ablates
    -- back to the res+cnt policy for the differential baseline.
    -- Mid-game kill-learning (ddaggi root cause #1). killSrc = nodes the opponent
    -- has a DEMONSTRATED live 한방 from (a dict-gap kill edge P->dead-Q our graph
    -- can't see). Landing the opponent on such P is opp-winning (sound: the kill
    -- edge is a real live move — see the design in project.md 밤8). HOSTILITY-GATED:
    -- injected only after a dict-gap word is observed this match (setHostile), so a
    -- default seat is byte-identical to plain play (zero EV loss vs average
    -- opponents the bot already beats). Seeded from data.seed_kill_sources if
    -- present; learned live via learnKill; persistence is the shell's job.
    -- opts.learnKills=false ablates the whole layer (kill-switch).
    self.learnKills = not (opts and opts.learnKills == false)
    self.killSrc = {}
    self.hostile = false
    -- Basin routing: the O(V+E) relabel is the INFINITE-supply approximation; it
    -- misses finite-supply parity that makes some static-UNKNOWN nodes exact-LOSS.
    -- The ddaggi expert's whole kill was herding the bot to 값 (node 244) — a
    -- single-escape "poisoned mouth" (only non-WIN move is 값표->표; 표 returns
    -- 표준값->값; once that one escape is spent 값 is WIN-only = LOSS). This pass
    -- detects that pattern LIVE (per current counts, so it correctly stops once the
    -- shuttle depletes) and re-propagates, so the bot routes AWAY from being herded
    -- into the basin. SOUND (proven parity, only forces genuine losses). Cheap: the
    -- scan is O(V*deg); re-propagation runs only when a live basin is found (rare).
    -- EXPERIMENTAL, default OFF: the theory + Python detection are validated (값 is
    -- the sole single-escape basin, herding 517), but (a) its benefit is offline-
    -- unmeasurable — no sim adversary reproduces the real expert's 값-herd — and
    -- (b) the Lua class-count detection still diverges from the word-count Python
    -- scan (does not yet catch 값 identically) and, when on, breaks the Lua/Python
    -- relabel differential (Python has no basin pass). Enable via opts.basinAware=
    -- true once the Lua↔Python parity is fixed AND a Python-side pass is added so
    -- the differential stays valid. Off => byte-identical to the verified bot.
    self.basinAware = (opts and opts.basinAware == true) or false
    if data.seed_kill_sources then
        for _, p in ipairs(data.seed_kill_sources) do self.killSrc[p] = true end
    end
    self.exact = not (opts and opts.exact == false)
    -- Dead-letter (한방) overlay — the CLASS-EQUIVALENCE BREAK (B2 soundness fix,
    -- ported from racesolver._apply_dead_kills; verified 32-flip full-supply
    -- oracle). A word whose RAW last syllable is a live-dead prompt (륨/늬/쏄) is an
    -- unconditional 한방: the arriver's raw prompt has ZERO live starters, yet the
    -- class graph folds that dead raw prompt onto a node with a LIVE sibling
    -- ending, so the class-count engine is blind to the kill. data.dead_kill maps
    -- node(1-based word_first) -> the dead-landing word strings played FROM it.
    -- DEFENSE: force those source nodes WIN + re-propagate (see _forceDeadKills).
    -- OFFENSE: emit a live dead word as a 한방 (see _buildChainQueue). ALWAYS-ON
    -- (dictionary fact, not hostility-gated); opts.deadKills=false ablates it to
    -- the pre-fix bytes for the differential's flag-OFF arm. Empty on toy dicts
    -- (no dead letters) => the toy chain differentials are unaffected.
    self.deadKills = not (opts and opts.deadKills == false)
    self.deadNodeWords = {}      -- node(1-based) -> {dead word strings}
    self.deadWordSet = {}        -- word string -> true (offense per-word check)
    if data.dead_kill then
        for k, words in pairs(data.dead_kill) do
            -- lua-literal payload keys are already numbers; JSON-decoded keys are
            -- strings — tonumber() normalizes both.
            local u = tonumber(k)
            self.deadNodeWords[u] = words
            for _, w in ipairs(words) do self.deadWordSet[w] = true end
        end
    end
    -- Live latency budget. TRIAL NOTE (2026-07-08 measurement): the old
    -- word-count gate (skip region if totalWords > 5000) was WRONG — it threw
    -- away the very wins it was meant to protect latency against. Measured on
    -- real kkeugeul full supply: of 70 sampled >5000-word regions, 20 (15 WIN /
    -- 5 LOSS) are DECIDED at budget 4000 in ~3-5ms (relabel cutoff short-circuits
    -- them); only the one ~9.4k-word blob stays UNPROVEN. The word gate discarded
    -- all 20 free wins to avoid the blob's ~1.6s exhaust-turn. Right fix: attempt
    -- EVERY region and bound worst-turn by a WALL-CLOCK DEADLINE — the fast wins
    -- finish in ms, the unprovable blob bails at the deadline (same UNPROVEN =>
    -- race-count fallback as before, just capped). This recovers the +10pp
    -- "large-region" contribution that combined-Rust had, in pure Luau (the wins
    -- need only budget 4000, not Rust; budget 4000 vs 20000 = 0 win delta, so
    -- attempting the region — not deep budget — was always the lever).
    self.exactBudget = (opts and opts.exactBudget) or 4000
    -- deadline (seconds) shared across a turn's whole exact solve (all safe
    -- children pool one budget). 0.7s << ~10s turn timer, >>100x the ~5ms a
    -- decided region needs => never clips a real win, only caps the blob.
    self.exactDeadline = (opts and opts.exactDeadline) or 0.7
    -- word gate kept as an OPTIONAL override (default effectively off); the
    -- deadline is now the real latency governor. 0/nil => off.
    self.exactMaxWords = (opts and opts.exactMaxWords) or 0
    self.n = data.meta.n_nodes
    self.nc = data.meta.n_classes

    -- outC[p] = classes with p in avail (fan-out); inC[t] = classes landing on t.
    local outC, inC = {}, {}
    for u = 1, self.n do outC[u] = {}; inC[u] = {} end
    for c = 1, self.nc do
        for _, p in ipairs(data.avail[c]) do
            outC[p][#outC[p] + 1] = c
        end
        local t = data.class_to[c]
        inC[t][#inC[t] + 1] = c
    end
    self.outC, self.inC = outC, inC

    self.staticLoss = {}
    for _, v in ipairs(data.static_loss) do self.staticLoss[v] = true end

    -- Opener pools + trap veto (first-player opener fix; see export_racebot /
    -- build_opener_pools). openerPools[node] = ordered vetted opener words (proven
    -- win first, neutral fallback; trap/유도/한방 landings pre-excluded). openerTraps
    -- is the set of landing nodes the exact engine proves are a MOVER-win, so
    -- landing the OPPONENT there is a proven LOSS for us (the 기윽 -> 윽윽 self-loop
    -- parity bug). Both are DATA-only for the policy (racebot's chain/queue tiers
    -- never touch them → the differential vs Python RaceSolver stays exact); the kt
    -- shell's pickForOpener/openerBanned consume them. Absent on toy dicts.
    self.openerPools = data.opener_pools or {}
    self.openerTraps = {}
    for _, v in ipairs(data.opener_traps or {}) do self.openerTraps[v] = true end

    self:reset()
    return self
end

-- ---------------------------------------------------------------- state --

function RaceBot:reset()
    local live, total = {}, {}
    for u = 1, self.n do total[u] = 0 end
    for c = 1, self.nc do
        local k = self.data.class_count[c]
        live[c] = k
        -- total mirrors state.live = g.starts_count: a word counts at EVERY
        -- position it can be played from (fan over all avail at INIT). Consume
        -- then decrements only the PRIMARY (word_first) — the documented
        -- conservative over-count (graph.py LIVE-COUNT CAVEAT).
        for _, p in ipairs(self.data.avail[c]) do total[p] = total[p] + k end
    end
    self.live, self.total = live, total
    self.used = {}          -- my accepted words (match scope)
    self.dead = {}          -- my rejected words (match scope)
    self.myLanding = nil    -- position my last accepted word landed on
    self.roundFresh = true
    self.iOpen = false
    self.pending = nil
    self.pendingCid = nil   -- exact class of the pending proposal (own play)
    self.queue, self.queueNote, self.queueCid, self.qi = {}, {}, {}, 0
    self.note = nil
    -- hostility is per-MATCH (escalate on first dict-gap word; stays for the
    -- match). killSrc is NOT cleared here — learned kills are durable across
    -- matches (the shell persists them to disk and re-seeds on load).
    self.hostile = false
    self.counters = { relabels = 0, oppInferred = 0, phantomOpeners = 0,
                      unknownTransitions = 0, rejects = 0, negClamped = 0,
                      killAvoids = 0, killsLearned = 0, deadKillSrcs = 0 }
end

function RaceBot:roundStart(iOpen)
    self.myLanding = nil
    self.roundFresh = true
    self.iOpen = iOpen and true or false
    self.pending = nil
    self.pendingCid = nil
    self.queue, self.queueNote, self.queueCid, self.qi = {}, {}, {}, 0
end

-- ------------------------------------------------ kill-learning API (shell) --
-- setHostile: called by the shell the FIRST time a live word outside our dict is
-- observed this match (RaceBot:consumePair returning false = the CLAMPED proof).
-- Activates kill-source avoidance for the rest of the match.
function RaceBot:setHostile()
    self.hostile = true
end

-- learnKill: called by the shell on a mid-game death — P is the node the bot last
-- landed the opponent on (RACE.myLanding), from which the opponent played a live
-- word into a structurally-dead syllable (the shell applies the structural-Q +
-- movesThisRound + life-drop guards; see the design). Durable in-memory; the
-- shell also persists P (raw) to disk and re-seeds on load.
function RaceBot:learnKill(p)
    if p and not self.killSrc[p] then
        self.killSrc[p] = true
        self.counters.killsLearned = self.counters.killsLearned + 1
    end
end

-- isKillLanding: is landing the OPPONENT on node v a known live-한방 for us?
-- Gated on learnKills (kill-switch) AND hostile (only avoid vs a proven-prepared
-- opponent — a default seat plays byte-identically). SOUND: v is a real live
-- kill-source, so treating "land opp on v" as opp-winning is the true L_opp value.
function RaceBot:isKillLanding(v)
    return self.learnKills and self.hostile and self.killSrc[v] == true
end

-- After relabel, force known kill-source nodes to WIN (hostile-gated). Landing the
-- opponent on a kill-source hands them a live 한방, so it is opp-WIN — the true
-- L_opp value our graph can't compute (the dict-gap kill edge isn't in it). Forcing
-- WIN makes the tier logic avoid landing there AND excludes it from CBRS regions
-- (_extractRegion pulls only UNKNOWN nodes) so the exact solver never routes a
-- FALSE win through a node the opponent actually kills from. SOUND: only ADDS
-- avoidance; a default (non-hostile) seat skips this so play stays byte-identical.
-- Post-relabel override — does NOT propagate backward (the corridor MOUTH isn't
-- auto-flagged; full synthetic-sink re-propagation is a documented follow-up).
-- Basin pass (single-escape poisoned-mouth parity). After the standard relabel,
-- find UNKNOWN nodes u whose ONLY live non-WIN escape is exactly k words to a single
-- DISTINCT node t, where t has >= k live words back to u. Then the mover at u must
-- spend its k escapes into t, the opponent returns each time, and once the escapes
-- are gone u is WIN-only => exact-LOSS (finite-supply parity the O(V+E) relabel
-- misses). Force those LOSS and re-run the retrograde wave. Modifies label/rank in
-- place. SOUND; byte-identical when no live basin exists (common case, cheap scan).
function RaceBot:_basinPass(label, rank)
    if not self.basinAware then return end
    local n, live = self.n, self.live
    local forced, nf = {}, 0
    for u = 1, n do
        if label[u] == UNKNOWN then
            local escT, escK, bad, multi = nil, 0, false, false
            for _, cid in ipairs(self.outC[u]) do
                if live[cid] > 0 then
                    local v = self.data.class_to[cid]
                    if label[v] == LOSS then bad = true; break       -- has 유도 (can't be)
                    elseif label[v] ~= WIN then                       -- non-WIN escape
                        if v == u then bad = true; break end          -- self-loop = tempo
                        if escT == nil then escT = v
                        elseif escT ~= v then multi = true; break end -- >1 escape target
                        escK = escK + live[cid]
                    end
                end
            end
            if (not bad) and (not multi) and escT then
                local rk = 0
                for _, cid in ipairs(self.outC[escT]) do
                    if live[cid] > 0 and self.data.class_to[cid] == u then rk = rk + live[cid] end
                end
                if rk >= escK then nf = nf + 1; forced[nf] = u end
            end
        end
    end
    if nf == 0 then return end
    -- re-propagate: retrograde wave with the stuck nodes AND the forced basins as
    -- LOSS sinks (mirror _relabel). Overwrites label/rank.
    local undec = {}
    for u = 1, n do
        local c = 0
        for _, cid in ipairs(self.outC[u]) do if live[cid] > 0 then c = c + 1 end end
        undec[u] = c
        label[u] = UNKNOWN; rank[u] = -1
    end
    local q, head = {}, 1
    for u = 1, n do
        if undec[u] == 0 then label[u] = LOSS; rank[u] = 0; q[#q + 1] = u end
    end
    for i = 1, nf do
        local u = forced[i]
        if label[u] ~= LOSS then label[u] = LOSS; rank[u] = 0; q[#q + 1] = u end
    end
    while head <= #q do
        local y = q[head]; head = head + 1
        for _, cid in ipairs(self.inC[y]) do
            if live[cid] > 0 then
                for _, x in ipairs(self.data.avail[cid]) do
                    if label[x] == UNKNOWN then
                        if label[y] == LOSS then
                            label[x] = WIN; rank[x] = rank[y] + 1; q[#q + 1] = x
                        else
                            undec[x] = undec[x] - 1
                            if undec[x] == 0 then
                                label[x] = LOSS; rank[x] = rank[y] + 1; q[#q + 1] = x
                            end
                        end
                    end
                end
            end
        end
    end
    self.counters.basinsForced = (self.counters.basinsForced or 0) + nf
end

function RaceBot:_forceKillSources(label, rank)
    if not (self.learnKills and self.hostile) then return end
    for p in pairs(self.killSrc) do
        if label[p] ~= WIN then
            label[p] = WIN
            if rank[p] == nil or rank[p] < 0 then rank[p] = 0 end
            self.counters.killAvoids = self.counters.killAvoids + 1
        end
    end
end

-- Live dead sources: nodes still holding an UNUSED dead word (a spent kill is not
-- a kill — the availability test that keeps the overlay sound). Mirrors
-- racesolver._live_dead_sources. used/dead are word-string sets (match scope).
function RaceBot:_liveDeadSources()
    local srcs, ns = {}, 0
    for u, words in pairs(self.deadNodeWords) do
        for _, w in ipairs(words) do
            if not self.used[w] and not self.dead[w] then
                ns = ns + 1; srcs[ns] = u; break
            end
        end
    end
    return srcs
end

-- Dead-letter synthetic-sink overlay (the class-equivalence fix). Ported verbatim
-- from racesolver._apply_dead_kills; SAME re-propagation shape as _basinPass. A
-- live dead-landing word is an unconditional 한방, so the node it is played FROM
-- (word_first) is a kill-source: force it WIN, then RE-RUN the retrograde wave over
-- the CURRENT residual live graph with those extra WIN seeds — a node whose every
-- live successor is now WIN becomes LOSS (a losing MOUTH that can only feed the
-- kill), which cascades WIN back to ITS predecessors. Rebuilt from scratch, NOT a
-- patch of `label`: a source can flip LOSS->WIN (a stuck-looking mouth that holds a
-- 한방), invalidating any predecessor WIN-certificate that leaned on it being LOSS —
-- only a fresh fixpoint is guaranteed sound. SOUND (T1-preserving): the seeds are
-- REAL wins (playing the live dead word ends the game on the spot), so every
-- WIN/LOSS in the fixpoint is true; the _liveDeadSources availability test is the
-- only precondition. Overwrites label/rank in place; a no-op leaving `label`
-- untouched when no source has a live word left (matches Python's early return).
function RaceBot:_forceDeadKills(label, rank)
    if not self.deadKills then return end
    local dead = self:_liveDeadSources()
    if #dead == 0 then return end
    local n, live = self.n, self.live
    local undec = {}
    for u = 1, n do
        local c = 0
        for _, cid in ipairs(self.outC[u]) do if live[cid] > 0 then c = c + 1 end end
        undec[u] = c
        label[u] = UNKNOWN; rank[u] = -1
    end
    local q, head = {}, 1
    -- Seed WIN first (rank 1) BEFORE the stuck-LOSS seeds: a source that were also
    -- stuck must stay WIN (the 한방 dominates). Matches the oracle's elif order.
    for _, u in ipairs(dead) do
        if label[u] ~= WIN then label[u] = WIN; rank[u] = 1; q[#q + 1] = u end
    end
    for u = 1, n do
        if label[u] == UNKNOWN and undec[u] == 0 then
            label[u] = LOSS; rank[u] = 0; q[#q + 1] = u
        end
    end
    while head <= #q do
        local y = q[head]; head = head + 1
        for _, cid in ipairs(self.inC[y]) do
            if live[cid] > 0 then
                for _, x in ipairs(self.data.avail[cid]) do
                    if label[x] == UNKNOWN then
                        if label[y] == LOSS then
                            label[x] = WIN; rank[x] = rank[y] + 1; q[#q + 1] = x
                        else
                            undec[x] = undec[x] - 1
                            if undec[x] == 0 then
                                label[x] = LOSS; rank[x] = rank[y] + 1; q[#q + 1] = x
                            end
                        end
                    end
                end
            end
        end
    end
    self.counters.deadKillSrcs = #dead
end

function RaceBot:_consume(cid)
    if self.live[cid] > 0 then
        self.live[cid] = self.live[cid] - 1
        -- decrement the PRIMARY source position only (mirror state.live).
        local f = self.data.avail[cid][1]
        self.total[f] = self.total[f] - 1
    else
        -- opponent played a word beyond our count for this class: our dict
        -- undercounts the live dict here. Clamp; strategy degrades gracefully.
        self.counters.negClamped = self.counters.negClamped + 1
    end
end

-- avail membership (small lists — linear scan is cheap). Used by opponent
-- transition inference to filter classes landing on v to those playable from
-- the source position myLanding.
local function availHas(av, p)
    for _, x in ipairs(av) do
        if x == p then return true end
    end
    return false
end

-- ------------------------------------------------- residual relabel core --
-- Port of residual.ResidualBoard.relabel: retrograde BFS where an edge exists
-- iff its class live count >= 1. rank = BFS wave (certificate length). A class
-- landing on y fans its verdict back to EVERY source in avail (refined).

function RaceBot:_relabel()
    local n, live = self.n, self.live
    local label, rank, undec = {}, {}, {}
    for u = 1, n do
        label[u] = UNKNOWN
        rank[u] = -1
        local c = 0
        for _, cid in ipairs(self.outC[u]) do
            if live[cid] > 0 then c = c + 1 end
        end
        undec[u] = c
    end
    local q, head = {}, 1
    for u = 1, n do
        if undec[u] == 0 then
            label[u] = LOSS; rank[u] = 0; q[#q + 1] = u
        end
    end
    while head <= #q do
        local y = q[head]; head = head + 1
        for _, cid in ipairs(self.inC[y]) do
            if live[cid] > 0 then
                for _, x in ipairs(self.data.avail[cid]) do
                    if label[x] == UNKNOWN then
                        if label[y] == LOSS then
                            label[x] = WIN; rank[x] = rank[y] + 1; q[#q + 1] = x
                        else
                            undec[x] = undec[x] - 1
                            if undec[x] == 0 then
                                label[x] = LOSS; rank[x] = rank[y] + 1
                                q[#q + 1] = x
                            end
                        end
                    end
                end
            end
        end
    end
    self.counters.relabels = self.counters.relabels + 1
    return label, rank
end

function RaceBot:_safeStats(label)
    local sw, sd = {}, {}
    for u = 1, self.n do sw[u] = 0; sd[u] = 0 end
    for c = 1, self.nc do
        local k = self.live[c]
        if k > 0 then
            local av = self.data.avail[c]
            local v = self.data.class_to[c]
            if label[v] == UNKNOWN then
                for _, u in ipairs(av) do sw[u] = sw[u] + k end
            end
            for _, u in ipairs(av) do
                if label[u] == UNKNOWN then sd[v] = sd[v] + k; break end
            end
        end
    end
    return { safeWords = sw, senders = sd }
end

-- Port of racesolver._race_key: counting score for a safe class u->v, lower is
-- better: (oppSafe, -floor, -senders). Final tiebreak is cid (offline engine
-- breaks ties by word index; cid order = first-occurrence word order, close
-- enough — divergence only on full-key ties). u = the position we play FROM.
function RaceBot:_raceKey(cid, label, stats, u)
    local v = self.data.class_to[cid]
    local oppSafe = stats.safeWords[v] - ((u == v) and 1 or 0)
    local floor = INF
    for _, c2 in ipairs(self.outC[v]) do
        local k = self.live[c2] - ((c2 == cid) and 1 or 0)
        if k > 0 then
            local x = self.data.class_to[c2]
            if label[x] == UNKNOWN then
                local fx = stats.safeWords[x] - ((x == u) and 1 or 0)
                if fx < floor then floor = fx end
            end
        end
    end
    local senders = stats.senders[v] - ((label[u] == UNKNOWN) and 1 or 0)
    return oppSafe, -floor, -senders
end

-- ============================================================ EXACT (CBRS) ==
-- Faithful port of kkutu_solver/cbrs.py CBRSSolver: delta-key memo + interior
-- T1 relabel cutoff over a residual UNKNOWN region. This is the exact layer the
-- prior live bot dropped ("minus the exact layer"); it is the measured lever
-- that beats the corridor exploit. SOUND: PWIN/PLOSS are unconditionally true;
-- budget exhaustion degrades to UNPROVEN (never a wrong verdict) and UNPROVEN is
-- never memoized. Verdicts are region-local RPWIN/RPLOSS/RUNPROVEN = 1/-1/0.
--
-- The DFS is ITERATIVE (explicit frame stack) on purpose: cbrs.py recursion hit
-- proof_depth 173950 in a match — native Luau recursion would overflow. Depth is
-- bounded by the visit budget (one new visit per depth level), so the frame
-- stack stays tiny in practice.

local RPWIN, RPLOSS, RUNPROVEN = 1, -1, 0

-- extract_region(root, label): BFS the UNKNOWN component reachable from root via
-- live classes, then build region-local structures (mirror residual.extract_region
-- + CBRSSolver.__init__). Returns nil if root is not UNKNOWN (nothing to solve).
function RaceBot:_extractRegion(root, label)
    if label[root] ~= UNKNOWN then return nil end
    local nid, nodes = {}, {}
    nid[root] = 1; nodes[1] = root
    local q, head = { root }, 1
    while head <= #q do
        local u = q[head]; head = head + 1
        for _, cid in ipairs(self.outC[u]) do
            if self.live[cid] > 0 then
                local v = self.data.class_to[cid]
                if label[v] == UNKNOWN and not nid[v] then
                    nodes[#nodes + 1] = v; nid[v] = #nodes; q[#q + 1] = v
                end
            end
        end
    end
    local nloc = #nodes
    -- rclasses: live classes landing INSIDE the region (dedup — a multi-source
    -- class appears in outC of every region node in its avail).
    local seen, rclasses = {}, {}
    for i = 1, nloc do
        for _, cid in ipairs(self.outC[nodes[i]]) do
            if self.live[cid] > 0 and nid[self.data.class_to[cid]] and not seen[cid] then
                seen[cid] = true; rclasses[#rclasses + 1] = cid
            end
        end
    end
    table.sort(rclasses)
    local slotOf, counts, totalWords = {}, {}, 0
    for s, cid in ipairs(rclasses) do
        slotOf[cid] = s; counts[s] = self.live[cid]; totalWords = totalWords + self.live[cid]
    end
    -- out[i] = {slot, targetLocal}; inn[t] = {slot, srcLocal}; one entry per
    -- in-region source of each class (exterior sources omitted — the region game
    -- only lets the token stand on region nodes).
    local out, inn = {}, {}
    for i = 1, nloc do out[i] = {}; inn[i] = {} end
    for s, cid in ipairs(rclasses) do
        local t = nid[self.data.class_to[cid]]
        for _, p in ipairs(self.data.avail[cid]) do
            local pl = nid[p]
            if pl then
                out[pl][#out[pl] + 1] = { s, t }
                inn[t][#inn[t] + 1] = { s, pl }
            end
        end
    end
    local function bySlot(a, b)
        if a[1] ~= b[1] then return a[1] < b[1] end
        return a[2] < b[2]
    end
    for i = 1, nloc do table.sort(out[i], bySlot); table.sort(inn[i], bySlot) end
    return { nid = nid, nodes = nodes, nloc = nloc, rclasses = rclasses,
             slotOf = slotOf, counts = counts, out = out, inn = inn,
             totalWords = totalWords, changed = {}, memo = {}, visits = 0,
             maxNodes = self.exactBudget, maxDepth = 0, exhausted = false }
end

-- region-restricted T1 retrograde relabel under CURRENT region counts. Edge
-- exists iff its class count >= 1; a node with no live region-internal move is
-- stuck == RPLOSS. Verbatim cbrs.py._relabel.
local function cbrsRelabel(R)
    local nloc, counts, out, inn = R.nloc, R.counts, R.out, R.inn
    local label, und = {}, {}
    local q, head = {}, 1
    for u = 1, nloc do
        local c = 0
        for _, e in ipairs(out[u]) do if counts[e[1]] > 0 then c = c + 1 end end
        und[u] = c
        if c == 0 then label[u] = RPLOSS; q[#q + 1] = u else label[u] = RUNPROVEN end
    end
    while head <= #q do
        local y = q[head]; head = head + 1
        local ly = label[y]
        for _, e in ipairs(inn[y]) do
            local slot, x = e[1], e[2]
            if counts[slot] > 0 and label[x] == RUNPROVEN then
                if ly == RPLOSS then
                    label[x] = RPWIN; q[#q + 1] = x
                else
                    und[x] = und[x] - 1
                    if und[x] == 0 then label[x] = RPLOSS; q[#q + 1] = x end
                end
            end
        end
    end
    return label
end

-- delta bookkeeping (counts + changed move in lockstep, mirror cbrs.py).
local function cbrsApply(R, slot)
    R.counts[slot] = R.counts[slot] - 1
    R.changed[slot] = (R.changed[slot] or 0) + 1
end
local function cbrsUnapply(R, slot)
    R.counts[slot] = R.counts[slot] + 1
    local c = R.changed[slot]
    if c == 1 then R.changed[slot] = nil else R.changed[slot] = c - 1 end
end

-- canonical memo key = (localNode, sorted(changed)). O(depth) entries.
local function cbrsKey(u, changed)
    local slots = {}
    for slot in pairs(changed) do slots[#slots + 1] = slot end
    table.sort(slots)
    local parts = {}
    for i, slot in ipairs(slots) do parts[i] = slot .. ":" .. changed[slot] end
    return u .. "|" .. table.concat(parts, ";")
end

-- iterative _solve: value for the MOVER at region-local node startLocal, under
-- the region's current counts. Shares R.memo/R.visits across sibling calls (the
-- budget is a single pool over all solve_child candidates, per cbrs.py).
function RaceBot:_cbrsSolveFrom(R, startLocal)
    local stack = { { u = startLocal, stage = "enter" } }
    local ret = RUNPROVEN
    while #stack > 0 do
        local fr = stack[#stack]
        if fr.stage == "enter" then
            -- latency governor: visit budget (deterministic) OR wall-clock
            -- deadline (set only for live turns via R.deadlineAt; nil in the
            -- differential test => that path stays byte-deterministic ==Python).
            -- Check the clock only every 256 visits to keep os.clock off the hot
            -- path. Both degrade to UNPROVEN, never a wrong verdict.
            if R.deadlineAt and R.visits % 256 == 0 and os.clock() >= R.deadlineAt then
                R.exhausted = true; ret = RUNPROVEN; stack[#stack] = nil
            elseif R.visits >= R.maxNodes then
                R.exhausted = true; ret = RUNPROVEN; stack[#stack] = nil
            else
                if #stack > R.maxDepth then R.maxDepth = #stack end
                local key = cbrsKey(fr.u, R.changed)
                local hit = R.memo[key]
                if hit ~= nil then
                    ret = hit; stack[#stack] = nil
                else
                    R.visits = R.visits + 1
                    local label = cbrsRelabel(R)
                    if label[fr.u] ~= RUNPROVEN then
                        ret = label[fr.u]; R.memo[key] = ret; stack[#stack] = nil
                    else
                        -- live out-edges; order UNKNOWN targets first, starve-first,
                        -- then slot (cbrs.py cands.sort).
                        local counts, out = R.counts, R.out
                        local cands = {}
                        for _, e in ipairs(out[fr.u]) do
                            if counts[e[1]] > 0 then cands[#cands + 1] = e end
                        end
                        local function livo(v)
                            local s = 0
                            for _, e in ipairs(out[v]) do s = s + counts[e[1]] end
                            return s
                        end
                        table.sort(cands, function(a, b)
                            local ka = (label[a[2]] == RUNPROVEN) and 0 or 1
                            local kb = (label[b[2]] == RUNPROVEN) and 0 or 1
                            if ka ~= kb then return ka < kb end
                            local la, lb = livo(a[2]), livo(b[2])
                            if la ~= lb then return la < lb end
                            return a[1] < b[1]
                        end)
                        fr.key = key; fr.cands = cands; fr.i = 1
                        fr.sawUnknown = false; fr.childActive = false
                        fr.stage = "loop"
                    end
                end
            end
        else    -- "loop"
            local popped = false
            if fr.childActive then
                cbrsUnapply(R, fr.appliedSlot)
                fr.childActive = false
                if ret == RPLOSS then       -- opponent loses at child => u wins
                    R.memo[fr.key] = RPWIN; ret = RPWIN
                    stack[#stack] = nil; popped = true
                elseif ret == RUNPROVEN then
                    fr.sawUnknown = true
                end
                if not popped then fr.i = fr.i + 1 end
            end
            if not popped then
                if fr.i <= #fr.cands then
                    local e = fr.cands[fr.i]
                    cbrsApply(R, e[1])
                    fr.appliedSlot = e[1]; fr.childActive = true
                    stack[#stack + 1] = { u = e[2], stage = "enter" }
                elseif fr.sawUnknown then
                    ret = RUNPROVEN; stack[#stack] = nil    -- never memoized
                else
                    R.memo[fr.key] = RPLOSS; ret = RPLOSS; stack[#stack] = nil
                end
            end
        end
    end
    return ret
end

-- solve_child(cid, v): value for the opponent at v (== class_to[cid]) after we
-- play one word of region class cid. Shares the memo across sibling candidates.
function RaceBot:_cbrsSolveChild(R, cid, v)
    local slot = R.slotOf[cid]
    if slot == nil or R.counts[slot] <= 0 then return RUNPROVEN end
    cbrsApply(R, slot)
    local r = self:_cbrsSolveFrom(R, R.nid[v])
    cbrsUnapply(R, slot)
    return r
end

-- --------------------------------------------------- candidate queues --

local function lex4(a, b)
    if a[1] ~= b[1] then return a[1] < b[1] end
    if a[2] ~= b[2] then return a[2] < b[2] end
    if a[3] ~= b[3] then return a[3] < b[3] end
    return a[4] < b[4]
end

function RaceBot:_pushPool(queue, notes, cids, cid, note, cap)
    local pool = self.data.pools[cid]
    if not pool then return end
    local added = 0
    for _, w in ipairs(pool) do
        if not self.used[w] and not self.dead[w] then
            queue[#queue + 1] = w
            notes[#notes + 1] = note
            cids[#cids + 1] = cid
            added = added + 1
            if cap and added >= cap then return end
        end
    end
end

-- Chain turn: port of racesolver.best_move tiers minus the exact layer
-- (RegionSolver is endgame-only and heavy; measured +11:0 on top of res+cnt's
-- 326:29 — cut from the live port, recorded trade-off). u = required position.
function RaceBot:_buildChainQueue(u)
    local label, rank = self:_relabel()
    -- Dead-letter DEFENSE overlay directly on the residual relabel (mirrors
    -- racesolver.best_move: board.relabel() -> _apply_dead_kills). Placed BEFORE
    -- basin/killSrc so the hostile killSrc WIN-patch composes on top of the
    -- dead-kill fixpoint (dead kills rebuild from scratch; killSrc only patches).
    self:_forceDeadKills(label, rank)
    self:_basinPass(label, rank)
    self:_forceKillSources(label, rank)
    local queue, notes, cids = {}, {}, {}
    local hanb, yudo, safe, risk = {}, {}, {}, {}
    -- OFFENSE overlay: a live pool word ending in a dead letter is an
    -- unconditional 한방 the class label can't see (class-equivalence break).
    -- Emit it FIRST (tier 0), before the class-tier buckets below. deadWordSet
    -- membership == racesolver.best_move's per-word `wi in _dead_word_idx` check;
    -- only emittable (in-pool, unused) words are scanned so the cid is always a
    -- real playable class. Empty deadWordSet (toy dicts / flag off) => no-op =>
    -- byte-identical to the pre-fix queue.
    if self.deadKills then
        for _, cid in ipairs(self.outC[u]) do
            if self.live[cid] > 0 then
                for _, w in ipairs(self.data.pools[cid] or {}) do
                    if self.deadWordSet[w] and not self.used[w]
                            and not self.dead[w] then
                        queue[#queue + 1] = w
                        notes[#notes + 1] = "한방"
                        cids[#cids + 1] = cid
                    end
                end
            end
        end
    end
    for _, cid in ipairs(self.outC[u]) do
        if self.live[cid] > 0 then
            local v = self.data.class_to[cid]
            -- opp count = state.live[v] minus 1 if this class's PRIMARY source
            -- (word_first = avail[cid][1]) is v itself (a self-loop the engine
            -- charges to v's own supply). Mirrors best_move word_first==v.
            local opp = self.total[v]
                - ((self.data.avail[cid][1] == v) and 1 or 0)
            if opp <= 0 then
                hanb[#hanb + 1] = { cid, 0, 0, cid }
            elseif label[v] == LOSS then
                yudo[#yudo + 1] = { rank[v], opp, 0, cid }
            elseif label[v] == WIN then
                -- killFlag sorts known-kill-source landings AFTER other risk
                -- (losing) landings: when forced to play a 위험 move, escape onto
                -- a non-mined landing (root cause #3). killFlag=0 for all when not
                -- hostile => byte-identical order (0-tiebreak, e[4]=cid unchanged).
                local killFlag = self:isKillLanding(v) and 1 or 0
                risk[#risk + 1] = { killFlag, -rank[v], opp, cid }
            else
                safe[#safe + 1] = cid
            end
        end
    end
    table.sort(hanb, lex4)
    table.sort(yudo, lex4)
    table.sort(risk, lex4)
    for _, e in ipairs(hanb) do
        self:_pushPool(queue, notes, cids, e[4], "한방")
    end
    for _, e in ipairs(yudo) do
        self:_pushPool(queue, notes, cids, e[4], "유도-res")
    end
    if #safe > 0 then
        local stats = self:_safeStats(label)
        local keyed = {}
        for _, cid in ipairs(safe) do
            local a, b, c = self:_raceKey(cid, label, stats, u)
            keyed[#keyed + 1] = { a, b, c, cid }
        end
        table.sort(keyed, lex4)
        -- EXACT layer (mirror racesolver._try_exact, cbrs engine): solve the
        -- UNKNOWN region for a PROVEN winning safe class (child PLOSS) and harvest
        -- disproofs (safe classes CBRS proves LOSE). The proven win goes first
        -- (race-exact); disproven classes drop to the back (never removed — a
        -- live-legal fallback must always remain, per trust+reject-adapt). Only
        -- when the required position is itself UNKNOWN (region-root requirement;
        -- if a 유도 exists u is WIN and was already queued above).
        local exactCid, losers = nil, {}
        if self.exact and label[u] == UNKNOWN then
            local R = self:_extractRegion(u, label)
            -- optional word gate (default off); the deadline below is the real
            -- governor. Stamp a per-turn wall-clock deadline shared across all
            -- child solves (they pool one visit budget too). _cbrsSolveFrom bails
            -- to UNPROVEN when it trips => same race-count fallback as a skip.
            if R and self.exactMaxWords and self.exactMaxWords > 0
               and R.totalWords > self.exactMaxWords then R = nil end
            if R then
                R.deadlineAt = os.clock() + self.exactDeadline
                for _, e in ipairs(keyed) do
                    local cid = e[4]
                    local r = self:_cbrsSolveChild(R, cid, self.data.class_to[cid])
                    if r == RPLOSS then exactCid = cid; break
                    elseif r == RPWIN then losers[cid] = true end
                end
            end
        end
        if exactCid then
            self:_pushPool(queue, notes, cids, exactCid, "race-exact")
        end
        for _, e in ipairs(keyed) do
            if e[4] ~= exactCid and not losers[e[4]] then
                self:_pushPool(queue, notes, cids, e[4], "race-count")
            end
        end
        for _, e in ipairs(keyed) do   -- disproven fallbacks, last resort
            if e[4] ~= exactCid and losers[e[4]] then
                self:_pushPool(queue, notes, cids, e[4], "race-count-disproven")
            end
        end
    end
    for _, e in ipairs(risk) do
        self:_pushPool(queue, notes, cids, e[4], "위험")
    end
    return queue, notes, cids
end

-- Round opener: port of racesolver.open_round. Tier 0 (residual-LOSS landing)
-- is a PROVEN win offline (T4) but its LIVE legality is the open rule question
-- — if the server re-checks 필승 on depleted state it just rejects, and this
-- queue falls through to tier 1 naturally.
function RaceBot:_pickOpenClass(v)
    local best, bestKey
    for _, cid in ipairs(self.inC[v]) do
        if self.live[cid] > 0 then
            -- a self-loop opener into v (class_to==v AND v in avail) eats one of
            -- v's own replies, so it needs total[v] >= 2 to clear the 한방 check.
            if not self.data.self_loop[cid] or self.total[v] >= 2 then
                local key = -self.live[cid] * (self.nc + 1) + cid
                if best == nil or key < bestKey then best, bestKey = cid, key end
            end
        end
    end
    return best
end

function RaceBot:_buildOpenQueue()
    local label, rank = self:_relabel()
    self:_basinPass(label, rank)
    self:_forceKillSources(label, rank)
    local stats = self:_safeStats(label)
    local queue, notes, cids = {}, {}, {}
    local t0, t1, t2 = {}, {}, {}
    for v = 1, self.n do
        if not self.staticLoss[v] and self.total[v] > 0 then
            if label[v] == LOSS then
                t0[#t0 + 1] = { rank[v], v, 0, v }
            elseif label[v] == UNKNOWN then
                t1[#t1 + 1] = { stats.safeWords[v], v, 0, v }
            else
                t2[#t2 + 1] = { -rank[v], v, 0, v }
            end
        end
    end
    table.sort(t0, lex4)
    table.sort(t1, lex4)
    table.sort(t2, lex4)
    if self.openProven then
        for _, e in ipairs(t0) do
            local cid = self:_pickOpenClass(e[2])
            if cid then
                self:_pushPool(queue, notes, cids, cid, "race-open-필승",
                               OPEN_WORDS_PER_NODE)
            end
        end
    end
    -- tier 1: refine the K best-starved nodes with the full 2-ply key. Opener is
    -- word-level (no single source node): feed _race_key the class's PRIMARY
    -- source avail[cid][1] for its O(1) herding corrections (heuristic only —
    -- opener soundness rides the LOSS/한방 tiers, not u). Mirrors open_round.
    local keyed, rest = {}, {}
    for i, e in ipairs(t1) do
        local v = e[2]
        local cid = self:_pickOpenClass(v)
        if cid then
            if i <= OPEN_TOPK then
                local a, b, c = self:_raceKey(cid, label, stats,
                                              self.data.avail[cid][1])
                keyed[#keyed + 1] = { a, b, c, cid }
            else
                rest[#rest + 1] = cid
            end
        end
    end
    table.sort(keyed, lex4)
    for _, e in ipairs(keyed) do
        self:_pushPool(queue, notes, cids, e[4], "race-open", OPEN_WORDS_PER_NODE)
    end
    for _, cid in ipairs(rest) do
        self:_pushPool(queue, notes, cids, cid, "race-open", OPEN_WORDS_PER_NODE)
    end
    for _, e in ipairs(t2) do
        local cid = self:_pickOpenClass(e[2])
        if cid then
            self:_pushPool(queue, notes, cids, cid, "race-open-버티기",
                           OPEN_WORDS_PER_NODE)
        end
    end
    return queue, notes, cids
end

-- ---------------------------------------------------------- public API --

function RaceBot:_next()
    local q = self.queue
    while self.qi < #q do
        self.qi = self.qi + 1
        local w = q[self.qi]
        if not self.used[w] and not self.dead[w] then
            self.pending = w
            self.pendingCid = self.queueCid[self.qi]
            self.note = self.queueNote[self.qi]
            return w
        end
    end
    self.pending, self.pendingCid, self.note = nil, nil, nil
    return nil
end

-- Opponent (non-opener) transition inference: opponent moved myLanding -> v.
-- Consume the max-live class landing on v that is playable from myLanding
-- (myLanding in avail). Sum-exact regardless of which class (only the consumed
-- COUNT matters for the live total); on dueum=False this is the unique (from,to)
-- class. Returns true if a class was consumed.
function RaceBot:_inferOppTransition(v)
    local from = self.myLanding
    local bigCid, bigK = nil, 0
    for _, cid in ipairs(self.inC[v]) do
        if self.live[cid] > bigK and availHas(self.data.avail[cid], from) then
            bigCid, bigK = cid, self.live[cid]
        end
    end
    if bigCid then
        self:_consume(bigCid)
        return true
    end
    return false
end

function RaceBot:myTurn(required)
    self.pending = nil   -- any unanswered previous proposal is void
    self.pendingCid = nil
    if required ~= nil then
        local v = self.data.syl2node[required]
        -- Opponent consumption inference happens HERE, before choosing.
        if self.roundFresh and not self.iOpen then
            -- opponent OPENED: start position unknown -> phantom-consume the
            -- largest live class landing at v (<=1 word/round error)
            if v then
                local bigCid, bigK = nil, 0
                for _, cid in ipairs(self.inC[v]) do
                    if self.live[cid] > bigK then
                        bigCid, bigK = cid, self.live[cid]
                    end
                end
                if bigCid then self:_consume(bigCid) end
                self.counters.phantomOpeners = self.counters.phantomOpeners + 1
            end
        elseif self.myLanding ~= nil then
            if v then
                if self:_inferOppTransition(v) then
                    self.counters.oppInferred = self.counters.oppInferred + 1
                else
                    -- transition absent from our dictionary: nothing to track
                    self.counters.unknownTransitions =
                        self.counters.unknownTransitions + 1
                end
            end
        end
        self.roundFresh = false
        if v then
            self.queue, self.queueNote, self.queueCid = self:_buildChainQueue(v)
        else
            -- required syllable's start-position has no words in our dict: we
            -- have nothing to play (한방 against us, or dict mismatch)
            self.queue, self.queueNote, self.queueCid = {}, {}, {}
        end
        self.qi = 0
    else
        self.roundFresh = false
        self.queue, self.queueNote, self.queueCid = self:_buildOpenQueue()
        self.qi = 0
    end
    return self:_next()
end

function RaceBot:accepted()
    local w = self.pending
    if not w then return end
    self.used[w] = true
    -- exact: consume the class we CHOSE (pendingCid), not a re-derived one.
    if self.pendingCid then self:_consume(self.pendingCid) end
    self.myLanding = self.data.syl2node[lastSyl(w)]
    self.pending, self.pendingCid = nil, nil
end

function RaceBot:rejected()
    local w = self.pending
    if w then
        self.dead[w] = true
        self.counters.rejects = self.counters.rejects + 1
    end
    return self:_next()
end

return RaceBot
end)()
